cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper involves the use of computer vision techniques for recognizing hand actions in RGB-D videos, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of robotics (cs.RO) for collecting the data and evaluating the results. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI) for action recognition and experimental evaluation. Finally, the paper also involves the use of 3D modeling and graphics (cs.GR) for providing 3D object models and visualizations.
